###Setting up a proportion

Corresponding sides of similar triangles are proportional, so we can set up and solve a proportion:

$\dfrac{\blueE{AW}}{ET}=\dfrac{PW}{PT}$

We picked side $\blueE{\overline{AW}}$ because we need to find its length.

We picked side $\overline{ET}$ because it corresponds to side $\blueE{\overline{AW}}$.

Then we picked another pair of corresponding sides where we already knew the measurements.

$\begin{array}{rcl}
&\triangle PAW
\\
{\text{opposite to } \atop \angle 3/\angle 4}
&\overbrace{\underbrace{\!\!\!\!\!\left\{ 
\dfrac{\blueE{AW}}{ET}=\dfrac{PW}{PT}
\right\}\!\!\!\!\!}}
&{\text{opposite} \atop \text{to }\angle A/\angle E}
\\
&\triangle PET
\end{array}$
